{
  "stem": "3952.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They gave us notice on Thursday that on Sunday we have to leave for the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Really, we didn't believe that this is going to happen.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Where are they going to take us?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, we believed that they are going to treat us like human beings, like-- like the neighbors we were.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But it wasn't to be.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Sunday morning, early they were starting hitting every soldier beside his rifle, these gendarmes had their sticks, and they were hitting with the sticks whatever would make noise just to put fear into us, and they rushed us out of the house and put everything, threw everything on that ox cart.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they took us at the other end of the city.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was about a mile and a half, I would say, that we walked a mile and a half.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They took us there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Were there-- in that ghetto, we were-- the whole of Sighet, all the people of Sighet were in a few-- well, were-- they-- they fenced off a few streets.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I remember the house of Elie Wiesel was the first house in that street to belong to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they lived-- actually, they were not going out of their house.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They lived in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were living in their house.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Only they added people to their-- to their-- you know, people were sleeping on the floor, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You couldn't have so many-- so many beds.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We happened to have some relatives, some cousins who lived in those streets that were included in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we went to live with them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I mean, they brought you into that-- into that area where the ghetto was, and they said, take your luggage and go.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They didn't tell you where to go, you just went.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
